<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Thy" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Thy,</orth> poss. pron. of the second pers. sing. (cf. <emph>Thou</emph>): <bibl n="shak. ven 12" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 12" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 12</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 12" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 12</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 12" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 12</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 12" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 12</bibl> 113 etc. etc. Before vowels: <bibl n="shak. ven 500" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 500</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 522" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 522</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 522" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 522</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 522" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 522</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 522" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 522</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 522" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 522</bibl> <bibl n="shak. son 4.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 4, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.2.112" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 2, 112</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.4.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 4, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 5.526" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 526</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 2, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.73.10" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 32</bibl> <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.197" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 1, 197</bibl> etc. More emphatical, in this case, than <emph>thine</emph>: <cit><quote>upon the earth's increase why shouldst thou feed, unless the earth with thy increase be fed?</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 170" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 170</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>yet for thy honour did I entertain him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 842" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 842</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>so sweet a kiss the golden sun gives not . . . as thy eye-beams,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.28" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 28</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>England knows thine insolence. And thy ambition, Gloster,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 1, 32</bibl></cit>.
